$interpreted: Servant: My lady, this is the last guest. The guests for today's birthday celebration were quite small in number.
Diana: ...It makes sense.
Diana: Everyone knows that uncle Andrew will succeed to the throne. Nobody wants to waste time forming a relationship with the loser.
Servant: My lady, don't you say that! The outcome is not yet clear...
Diana: Ever since the Border Wars was lost, the old king had to step down.
Diana: The battle for the throne has already raged on for 10 years. It's time for this to end.
Diana: Cousin Cecilia was stabbed to death last week and cousin Sydney was killed yesterday, removing them from the competition.
Diana: I'm uncle Andrew's last impediment to the throne.
Servant: My lady...you're the final hope for the Juan family. Please don't be so disheartened...eh?
Diana: Wh-What is it?
Servant: My lady, is your left-hand hurting? I often see you rubbing it with a look of discomfort.
Diana: It's just a habit, that's all! It's nothing.
Servant: But——
Guest: Sorry! There was a delay on the road. Apologies for the late arrival. I've come for Diana's birthday celebration. Here's my invitation.
Guest: I'm not too late, am I?
Servant: The invitation is correct. You nearly missed it.
Servant: My lady, see, there are still more guests~
Guest: Miss Diana Juan Gomez, my master wanted to give you this Ganophyllite stone, as it is the same color as your eyes.
Guest: May this simple gift express our heart's intention. The Haarjhinu family wishes you a happy birthday.
Servant: My lady, it's really a Ganophyllite stone! Even the nation's treasury only holds two of these!
Diana: Please thank the Haarjhinu family for me. I shall receive the gift.
Guest: You...!
Lazer: Shh.
Lazer: Do you hear that ticking?
Lazer: A Ganophyllite stone that can kill. I'm guessing even the national treasury doesn't have such a stone.
Guest: N-N-N-No, this is a misunderstanding. I didn't know there was anything wrong with the stone.
Lazer: Speak. You're either an impersonator...or perhaps you are an assassin sent by the Haarjhinu family?
Guest: Damn! Almost had it...!
Guest: Might as well——
Guest: DIE!!!!
Guest: Your moves...! No! Diana Juan doesn't practice martial arts...
Guest: *tsk*...tricked! You're not the real thing!
Servant: What did you say!?
Lazer: Child, do not let him escape!
Diana: Yes!
Lazer: Did you hear what that assassin just said?
Servant: Please, sir! I won't say a word! Not a word!
Servant: My lady, help! I'm begging you——
Lazer: You are not her lady. The Juan family has a policy: whoever knows this secret must die.
Diana: ...Yes, teacher.
Lazer: Don't call me teacher. It makes me uncomfortable.
Lazer: However, looks like you'll need to learn more about precious stones.
Lazer: It's a valuable mineral, abundant in the Desert Kingdom. As a member of the royal family, you must know the difference between Ganophyllite and a Clover Crystal.
Diana: ...Clover Crystal?
Lazer: It's a cheap ore, also known as counterfeit Ganophyllite. Though its color resembles Ganophyllite, its degree of purity pales in comparison.
Lazer: If you look closely, you can see the flaws and impurities, no?
Lazer: With the noble name of Gomez, you must be able to distinguish between the two. Be more careful next time.
Diana: ...Understood.
Lazer: Tomorrow's practice will carry on as usual. I shall take my leave first.
Diana: ...Counterfeit...
Diana: Against the light of the moon, it's still so pretty...
